===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# [[fragmented|Fragmented]], in separate pieces.
# {{qualifier|of a body part}} Having the bone in pieces, [[fractured]].
#: ''My arm is '''broken'''''
# {{qualifier|of skin}} Split or [[ruptured]].
#: ''A dog bit my leg and now the skin is '''broken'''.''
# Not [[working]] properly.
#: ''I think my shaver is '''broken'''.''
# Completely [[defeated]] and [[dispirited]].
#: ''The bankruptcy and divorce, together with the death of his son, left him completely '''broken'''.''
# {{pejorative|of language}} [[grammatical|Grammatically]] non-standard, especially as a result of being a [[non-native speaker]].
# Having no money, [[bankrupt]], [[broke]].
# {{qualifier|of an electronic connection}} [[disconnected|Disconnected]], no longer open or carrying traffic.
# {{rfv-sense}} [[degraded|Degraded]], reduced in rank
# {{software|informal}} [[badly|Badly]] [[designed]] or [[implemented]].
#: ''This is the most '''broken''' application I've seen in a long time.''
# {{meteorology|of the sky}} Five [[eighth]]s to seven eighths [[obscure|obscured]] by clouds.
#: ''Tomorrow '''broken''' skies..''
# {{sports|and|gaming}} A single [[tactic]] or [[option]] which is powerful enough to be considered [[overpowered]].
# {{colloquial|US}} A situation that has not gone in the way intended, [[saddening]].
#: ''Oh man! That is just '''broken'''!''

